**Executive Summary:** An unauthorized actor accessed the production database via a compromised service account whose credentials were accidentally exposed in a public GitHub repository, exfiltrating 12,400 user records containing names, emails, and bcrypt-hashed passwords. The incident was detected and contained within 6.5 hours; credentials were rotated, MFA enforcement enabled, affected users notified, and regulatory filings completed.
